isis.stitle: TSI 95-12-08 - Release Performance Data Guidelines For 1994/1995 International 530 Diesel Engines

subjectgroup.subject: Release Performance Data Guidelines For 1994/1995 International 530 Diesel Engines

svcproc.title: SUBJECT DESCRIPTION
svcproc.para: Engine Performance Data Guidelines are being released to service for the following International® 530 engine models beginning with Engine Serial No. 908390.

svcprocinfo.para: File a copy of this bulletin in Section 5, of Diesel Engine Diagnostic Manual, EGES-110.

svcsubproc.title: The International® 530/250 HP @ 2000 RPM w/Bowden Wire Shut-Off or Electric Shut-Off [50 State 1994/1995 Model Year]

para.emph: The International® 530/250 HP @ 2000 RPM w/Bowden Wire Shut-Off or Electric Shut-Off [50 State 1994/1995 Model Year]

entry.para: Injection Pump Part Number Original Equipment
Injection Nozzle Part Number Original Equipment
Nozzle Valve Opening Pressure New or Reconditioned
Nozzle Valve Minimum Opening Pressure Before Replacement
Intake and Exhaust Valve Clearance (Engine Off - Hot or Cold)
The following data to be taken at high idle with [no load].
Air Cleaner Restriction* [Measured @ Air Cleaner Outlet]
(Check at Full Load, Rated Speed) - Max
The following data to be taken at full load, full throttle rated engine speed on chassis dynamometer or on highway
Measure water temperature differential across the radiator with engine on a chassis dynamometer, at full load and ambient temperature of 80°F or above.
The following data to be taken after engine reaches stabilized operating temperature.
Lube Oil Pressure at Operating Temperature
*Engine must be at normal operating temperature.
**Crankcase pressure [ maximum ] as measured with Orificed Restrictor Tool ZTSE4039.
